{
  "texts": [
    "We refer to their respective manuscripts for detailed descriptions of the different counterfactual algorithms.",
    "Moreover, we also look at their disagreement with both SHAP and Anchors.",
    "As we mentioned in Sect. 2.2, there is no consensus on what defines the quality of a counterfactual explanation, which resulted in many algorithms optimizing explanations for different evaluation metrics.",
    "When we compare algorithms optimized or evaluated for other metrics, some form of disagreement is expected.",
    "However, when comparing explanations from algorithms that optimize for the same metric, one might expect less disagreement."
  ]
}